To build from source on UNIX(BSD, Linux, OSX, Solaris), run the build/build
script. This configures your system specific development tools, builds the
stdapi shared library and compiles all test programs

To build on UNIX from distribution, run configure and then make

To build on UNIX with Eclipse, run configure and then load the project

To build on OSX with XCode, use the build/Blister.xcworkspace project file

To build on Windows with Visual Studio, use the build/Blister.sln project file

